SQL - Structured Query Language : An Organized collection of data stored in an electronic format 
                                  A standard language for accessing and manipulating the data of a particular relational database.
                                 
   COMMANDS : DDL, DCL, DML, TCL, DQL
              ~ DDL - Data Definition Language: 
                      Create - Create Database database_name;
                      Create table table_name;
                      Create view view_name;
                      
                      Drop - Drop database_name;
                             Drop Table_name;
                             
                      Alter -  ALTER TABLE table_name ADD column_name Datatype; 
                      
                      Truncate - It used to delete all the rows from the table and free the space containing the table.
                                 TRUNCATE TABLE table_name;  
                                 
   
